The blood pressure standardization for the BP monitor has been guided and developed according to WHO classification.

The Dr. Morepen BP-06 automatic BP monitor incorporates an Irregular heartbeat indicator that identifies possible irregularity or disturbance in heartbeat rhythms.   • Compressor Nebulizer
  • 4 micro m MMAD

Dr. Morepen CN 05 Palm Compressor Nebulizer provides you with quick and effective delivery of medication to bring about a remedial solution for mild or serious respiratory conditions. The compressor unit of this nebulizer fits in the palm of your hands thus enhancing its portability factor.

This Nebulizer uses compressed air or oxygen to break the liquid medication into fine mist or aerosol droplets which can be easily inhaled into your lungs through a nozzle or mouthpiece.

Body

Conceptualized to meet easy and comfortable standards the Dr. Morepen palm compressor nebulizer is lightweight and compact allowing you to carry the device with you even if you are travelling. This compressor nebulizer delivers a systematic operation which has four main parts to complete the nebulization process. The four main parts comprises of the compressor unit air tube medication cup and a mouthpiece. Face masks can be alternately used along with the mouthpiece.

The portable compressor unit delivers oxygen to the medication cup through the 2 m air tube. Functioning with a sound level below 48 dB this compressor unit allows for a very quiet operation. The compressor unit houses an easy one touch operation button and a connector. The air tube is inserted into the connector linking the unit to the medication cup and mouthpiece. The medication cup can hold 6 ml of the prescribed solution which is aerosolized when the oxygen passes through it. You can inhale this aerosolized medication through the mouthpiece which is comfortable and easy to use.

Performance and Features

This CN 05 compressor nebulizer by Dr. Morepen operates with an average nebulization rate of 0.5 ml thus bringing about a desired effect by delivering the right amount of medication to your lungs. The air or oxygen in the compressor unit flows towards the medication cup at a rate of 6 to 8 l/min. This air or oxygen then passes through the medication solution at a rate of 6 l/min thus producing high concentration of aerosolized droplets.

The air that enters into the medication cup pulverizes and turns the liquid solution into fine aerosol droplets. These fine aerosols are quantified in terms of pulverization amount. This palm compressor nebulizer is capable of producing 0.15 ml of the pulverization amount. The Mass Median Aerodynamic Diameter (MMAD) which is the average distribution of aerosol mass with respect to aerodynamic diameter is 4 Î¼m.

Dr. Morepen CN 05 compressor nebulizer operates at a temperature ranging from 10 degree Celsius to 40 degree Celsius with humidity ranging from 10% to 95% RH. You can store this nebulizer at a temperature ranging from 20 degree Celsius to 70 degree Celsius and humidity ranging from 10 to 95% RH. Powered by electricity the palm compressed nebulizer requires a power supply of AC 100 to 250 V or DC 12 V.

Dr. Morepen CN 01 Compressor Nebulizer could assist you in improving and controlling respiratory related problems and ailments. This nebulizer uses compressed air or oxygen to atomize liquid solutions into fine vapor mist that is easily inhaled thereby effectively delivering medication to your lungs.

Capable of delivering medication to both your upper and lower respiratory track this Dr. Morepen compressor nebulizer is efficient and reliable. The nebulization process quickly and effectively delivers the medication to your lungs leading to a shorter inhalation time.

Body

Weighing about 2100 g this Dr. Morepen compressor nebulizer is small and compact. Designed with simplicity this nebulizer includes four components comprising of the compressor unit air tube nebulizer or medication cup and mouthpiece. The compressor unit has an in-built storage space for all the components hence providing you with enhanced portability.

The compressor unit capably supplies compressed air or oxygen to the medication cup through the tubing. This oxygen then passes through the medication cup and converts the liquid solution to aerosol mist. The nebulizer cup holds 5 ml of medication solution. The converted aerosol is then inhaled by you through the mouthpiece that has to be placed properly in your mouth to avoid medical wastage.

This nebulizer by Dr. Morepen is extremely safe as the nebulizer is autoclavable. Autoclaves are used to sterilize the device in order to neutralize potentially infectious agents by subjecting the device to high saturated heat. Due to this heat some devices cannot be sterilized as they are unable to withstand the heat. However this CN 01 Dr. Morepen nebulizer can endure the high saturated heat allowing a complete sterilization thus meeting hygiene and safety standards. This compressed nebulizer comes with inter changeable jet caps so if your cap is damaged or dirty you can replace it with a new one.

Dr. Morepen CN 01 nebulizer functions with an average nebulization rate of 0.2 ml supplying the right amount of medication that reaches your lungs. The compressed air or oxygen that streams its way from the compressor unit flows through the medication cup at a pressure rate of 8 to 16 psi.The oxygen in the nebulizer is capable of turning the liquid solution into aerosol or particle sizes ranging from 0.5 to 10 ?m. The particle size is minute enough to reach the narrow branches of your lower airways. The Mass Median Aerodynamic Diameter (MMAD) is 4 ?m.

This compressor nebulizer operates at a temperature ranging from 10 to 40 deg Celsius with humidity ranging from 10 to 95% RH. Storing the Nebulizer machine would be ideal at a temperature ranging from 20 to 70 deg Celsius and humidity ranging from 10 to 95% RH. The Dr. Morepen compressor nebulizer is powered by electricity. The device consumes 180 W of electricity from a power supply of 230 V or 50 Hz.
